STEP 4: PHYSICAL ORIGIN OF EACH PIECE
------------------------------------------------------------------------

  Piece                  Origin
  ---------------------- --------------------------------------------------
  197/144                Algebraic reduction of 7 two-loop diagrams
                         197 is prime. 144 = 2⁴×3² = 12².
                         No transcendental content — pure counting.

  (3/4)ζ(3)              Feynman parameter integral over polylogarithms
                         Li₃(1) = ζ(3) at integration boundary x=1.
                         Coefficient 3/4 is rational from diagram topology.

  R₄×(8/3)               4D momentum phase space integral
                         ∫d⁴k → π² = 32R₄ from solid angle in 4D.
                         The 8/3 comes from angular integration limits.

  R₄×(−16ln2)            Infrared mass singularity regulation
                         Electron mass regulates IR → ln(m²/μ²) → ln(2).
                         16 = 2⁴ from diagram topology.

STEP 5: THE CANCELLATION STRUCTURE
------------------------------------------------------------------------

  A₂ = +1.368 + 0.902 − 2.598 = −0.328

  The positive pieces (+2.270) are 87% of the geometric piece (2.598).
  The net A₂ is only 13% of either side of the cancellation.

  This means: the 2-loop QED correction to (g−2) is accidentally small.
  It's small not because the physics is small, but because geometry
  (4D phase space) nearly cancels the combinatorics (diagram counting)
  and number theory (polylogarithm integrals).

  In the HOWL language: R₄ (Level 1 geometric structure) nearly
  cancels the Level 2 content (rational + number-theoretic).
  The remaining −0.328 is the net effect after cancellation.

STEP 6: CONNECTION TO AMPLITUDES LITERATURE
------------------------------------------------------------------------

  The decomposition A₂ = rational + ζ(3) term + R₄ term is a
  specific instance of the general separation studied by Brown,
  Schnetz, and Panzer in their work on the Galois coaction of
  multiple zeta values in perturbative QFT.

  Their framework: Feynman integrals decompose into 'periods'
  (geometric integrals over moduli spaces) and 'coefficients'
  (arithmetic data from the motivic structure). The Galois
  coaction separates these systematically.

  The HOWL decomposition maps onto this as:
    R₄ content  ←→  period (geometric, from spacetime dimension)
    ζ(3) content ←→  arithmetic (from polylogarithm depth)
    197/144      ←→  rational coefficient (diagram combinatorics)

  At 3-loop (A₃), the decomposition becomes richer:
    R₄ appears with new coefficients
    R₄² = (π²/32)² appears (products of periods)
    ζ(5) appears (deeper polylogarithm)
    Li₄(1/2) appears (polylogarithm at non-trivial argument)
    Products like R₄×ζ(3) appear (period × arithmetic)

  The geometric and arithmetic content multiply but remain
  separable — they sit in different factors of each term.
  The R₂/R₄ language makes the geometric factor explicit
  in every term, connecting HOWL to this program.

